# .worktreeinclude — gitignored local docs that every parallel worktree needs
# for full context. Synced by scripts/sync-worktree-docs.ps1 <worktree-path>
# after a worktree is created from origin/main.
#
# RULE: NEVER list secrets here (appsettings.Local.json, .env.local, *.pem,
# *.tfstate). Only the stack-owner main checkout runs against real secrets;
# the sync script refuses secret-like entries.
#
# Entries may be files, directories, or globs (resolved relative to repo root).

# Session-state source of truth (gitignored, ADR 0072 docs-privacy)
docs/current-work.md
docs/current-work-archive.md
docs/steg-tracker.md
docs/tech-debt.md
docs/tech-debt-archive.md

# Per-session logs + local agent reviews + local ADRs for context.
# (Globs match ADR 0070–0199; already-tracked 0070–0073 are already present in
# the worktree, so re-copying them is redundant but harmless. The 01-glob was
# added 2026-07-10 with ADR 0100, parity with .gitignore.)
docs/sessions/
docs/reviews/
docs/decisions/00[789][0-9]-*.md
docs/decisions/01[0-9][0-9]-*.md

# GDPR Art. 30 processing-register (ROPA) — local-only (ADR 0072 / #183), internal
# accountability record. Worktrees need it for GDPR context; never a secret.
docs/runbooks/gdpr-processing-register.md
